transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, this is Viagra.

Speaker 2: Yeah, anybody like to cancel a prescription?

Speaker 1: Okay, let me fill your prescription. Mr. Terry Sturby?

Speaker 2: That's correct.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Yeah, I see that you have a prescription from Dr. Blackwell for Viagra 50 mg, 10 tablets, I think every 30 days.

Speaker 1: You just don't need refill?

Speaker 2: No, I don't.

Speaker 1: Okay, I can advise the pharmacy to stop the initial 30 days and you can just order as needed because you don't have to get it every 30 days.

Speaker 2: That was just the initial written prescription.

Speaker 1: Okay, I only want it when I order it.

Speaker 2: Yes, yes, so they're going to pause just to preserve the prescription they financed for you,

Speaker 1: but I'm going to tell them to stop the initial 30 days because when let's say you don't need pills, we're not going to send pills,

Speaker 2: extra pills every month, you haven't finished what you have.

Speaker 1: You just got to let us know so we advise the pharmacy, okay?

Speaker 2: Some patients are more active than others.

Speaker 1: We just got to have the information to make adjustment for you.

Speaker 2: All right, let me advise the pharmacy they're going to pause.

Speaker 1: To lock your pricing, you can just get maybe a refill once or twice a year, but no more every 30 days, you know what I mean?

Speaker 2: Sounds good.

Speaker 1: All right, let me put a pause on that.

Speaker 2: They'll pause you up to half a year so you don't have monthly anymore, okay?

Speaker 1: Okay, can I get an email or something on this?

Speaker 2: Yeah, yeah, you can get that.

Speaker 1: Give me one moment.

Speaker 2: Do you want me to give you also maybe a confirmation number?

Speaker 1: Sure, let me find something to write it down.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Let's see here.

Speaker 2: Okay, I'm ready.

Speaker 1: All right, so two.

Speaker 2: Two.

Speaker 1: E like eagle.

Speaker 2: E, got it.

Speaker 1: Yeah, A like alpha.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: E like frank.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Seven, three.

Speaker 2: Seven, three.

Speaker 1: C like Charlie.

Speaker 2: Got it.

Speaker 1: D like delta.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: And the number three, eight.

Speaker 2: So yeah, your prescription is paused and call us to reorder, okay?

Speaker 1: I'll get you a refill once or twice a year.

Speaker 2: Okay, can I read that back to you real quick?

Speaker 1: Yes, please.

Speaker 2: E, A, F, seven, three, C, D, three, eight.

Speaker 1: Yes, sir.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: Yeah, so you're all set for now, okay?

Speaker 1: And press your quick refill button in your account or give us a call to,

Speaker 2: you know, get your 10 pills.

Speaker 1: But, you know, you're not going to get it on the monthly.

Speaker 2: If you want to reinstate the monthly,

Speaker 1: you can let us know as well in the future because you have a VIP account,

Speaker 2: so you can manage your prescription at your liking, okay?

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Sounds great.

Speaker 1: You're all set, sir.

Speaker 2: You have a good one.

Speaker 1: Yeah, you too.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.
